{"word":"τμητός","slug":"τμητός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τμητός</b></el> <el>(τμητός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>τέμνω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>cut, shaped by cutting</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>that can be cut</i> or <i>severed</i>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}